==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: manna grass
<hw>manna grass</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <def>Any of
several tall slender grasses of the genus <gen>Glyceria</gen>. They have
long loose panicles, have a sweet flavor or odor, and grow in moist
places. <stype>Nerved manna grass</stype> is <spn>Glyceria
nervata</spn>, and <stype>Floating manna grass</stype> is <spn>Glyceria
fluitans</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manna gum</ent>⟦br⟧
